		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have soloed a human warrior from level 1 to 42. Here is where I hunted. Hunt blue, white cons and yellow cons if ya got good equipment however when you hit teens, do not solo yellows unless your very twinked. Someone gave me a Minotaur Axe :) Slow but excellent for level 1 :)<br><br>Level 1-6: North Ro (I made level 6 in under an hour)<br><br>Level 6-10: Feerot Lizards on pyramids near CT<br><br>Level 10-13: Orc Camps in South Ro (solo orcs)<br><br>Level 13-17: Oasis Caiman & Crocs (no deeps)<br><br>Level 17-19: Rathe Mountains (On Bears)<br><br>Level 19-24: Solo Aviak Spawn in Lake Rathetear<br><br>Level 24-29: South Karana (Gnolls and Aviaks)<br><br>Alternative 24-29: Forest Giants in Warslicks Woods & Lake of Ill Omen<br><br>Level 29-37: Everfrost (Mammoths, Tainted Mammoth & Corrupted Mammoth, Martar Icebear)<br><br>Level 37-42: Fironia Vie (Blue Con Growlers & Snarlers & Goblins) (I have Journeyman Boots), Some snarlers still con blue. I can solo giants at giant camp at 42 IF I have help breaking up the spawn at the camp. <br><br>Some advice:<br>To make money I hunt mammoths and sell their tusks in everfrost and can make quite a nice amount of plat in a day of money hunting. There are other ways as well.<br><br>Buy Potions and use them. Too many warriors do not use potions. If you do not have Journeyman boots then buy some SOW potions. Buy some healing potions as well. Example, You need to get thru tricky area, sow potion + invisible potion will usualy get you thru tho carry spares, I found the invis postions act like the spells and can go off at any time.<br><br>Use bandage skill. I found that I have it maxed at 100 for now, and it helps cut time down alot. <br><br>Try to get a Sewn Evil Eye bag, buy it or loot it. Helps alot. Also buy handmade backpacks. 10 Spots comes in handy. <br><br>If you want to be a warrior, and want less downtime, troll warrior is pretty good for that as is iksar. But it is personal preference. If not then try to get iksar ceremonial or fungi bp or even rubicite if any are being sold. Bring lots of plat however.<br><br>For weapons, try this.<br><br>At level 20 you may need some help. Do the Dwarven Avenger Axe quest. A 15 damage, magic axe with nice + to stats (check item area for info). <br><br>At level 24 do the Hallas Langseax quests. Try to get two Langseax shortswords and the 2 hand Langseax of the wolves sword. These are great and underrated weapons. Perfect for non twinked warriors who want to get decent weapons on their own. Check Alla quest section for details.<br><br><br>Good luck<br><br>Illbart Daddo<br>42nd Level Warrior<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
